## Task 2: Create builder/editors/SharedFields.tsx

A component that renders fields common to all step types:

Props: `{ step: PipelineStep; onUpdate: (patch: Partial<PipelineStep>) => void; position: 'top' | 'bottom' }`

When position='top':
- Label/Objective input using `.builder-section` + `.builder-input` CSS classes

When position='bottom':
- On Failure dropdown (retry/skip/halt/escalate) using `.builder-section` + `.builder-select`
- Retry Count input (only shown when onFailure === 'retry') using `.builder-input` type=number

Import PipelineStep from '../stepTypes'.

## Task 3: Create builder/useIntegrations.ts

Hook that fetches `GET /api/integrations` on mount:

```typescript
export interface Integration {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  provider: string;
  capabilities: string[];
  auth_status: string;
  icon: string;
}

export function useIntegrations(): { integrations: Integration[]; loading: boolean }
```

The API returns `{ integrations: [...], count: N }`. Follow the exact pattern in `useModels.ts` (useState + useEffect + useCallback).

## Task 4: Create builder/useObjectTypes.ts

Hook that fetches `GET /api/object-types` on mount:

```typescript
export interface ObjectType {
  type_id: string;
  name: string;
  description: string;
  icon: string;
  property_definitions: any[];
}

export function useObjectTypes(): { objectTypes: ObjectType[]; loading: boolean }
```

The API returns `{ types: [...], count: N }`. Same pattern as useModels.ts.

