## Task 1: Create builder/editors/TriggerEditor.tsx

Simple editor for trigger steps. Props: `{ step: PipelineStep; onUpdate: (patch: Partial<PipelineStep>) => void }`

Sections:
- Event Type: select (webhook, schedule, email, file_upload, database_change, manual)
- Source: input placeholder "Where do events come from?"
- Filter Condition: input placeholder "When should this trigger fire?"

Use builder-section, builder-section__label, builder-input, builder-select CSS classes.

## Task 2: Update BuilderPage.tsx

Read BuilderPage.tsx fully first. Find the editor panel section (inside `panelTab === 'edit'`).

Replace ALL the inline editor sections (the large block of step-type-specific inputs) with imports from the new editor components:

```tsx
import { SharedFields } from './editors/SharedFields';
import { CheckEditor } from './editors/CheckEditor';
import { HumanEditor } from './editors/HumanEditor';
import { ApiEditor } from './editors/ApiEditor';
import { AgentEditor } from './editors/AgentEditor';
import { TriggerEditor } from './editors/TriggerEditor';
```

The edit tab content becomes:
```tsx
{panelTab === 'edit' && (
  <div style={{ padding: 16, display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: 12, overflowY: 'auto', flex: 1 }}>
    <SharedFields step={selectedStep} onUpdate={(patch) => handleUpdateStep(selectedStep.id, patch)} position="top" />

    {selectedStep.stepType === 'agent' && (
      <AgentEditor step={selectedStep} onUpdate={(patch) => handleUpdateStep(selectedStep.id, patch)} />
    )}
    {selectedStep.stepType === 'check' && (
      <CheckEditor step={selectedStep} onUpdate={(patch) => handleUpdateStep(selectedStep.id, patch)} />
    )}
    {selectedStep.stepType === 'api' && (
      <ApiEditor step={selectedStep} onUpdate={(patch) => handleUpdateStep(selectedStep.id, patch)} />
    )}
    {selectedStep.stepType === 'human' && (
      <HumanEditor step={selectedStep} onUpdate={(patch) => handleUpdateStep(selectedStep.id, patch)} />
    )}
    {selectedStep.stepType === 'trigger' && (
      <TriggerEditor step={selectedStep} onUpdate={(patch) => handleUpdateStep(selectedStep.id, patch)} />
    )}

    <SharedFields step={selectedStep} onUpdate={(patch) => handleUpdateStep(selectedStep.id, patch)} position="bottom" />
  </div>
)}
```

Remove the now-unused imports: `useModels` (moved to AgentEditor), `useSystemStatus` only if it was only used for the toolbar metrics (check if it's still used in the toolbar section — if yes, keep it).

Do NOT change the Preview tab, the panel header, the pipeline canvas, or the toolbar.

## Task 3: Update queueSpecExport.ts

Read queueSpecExport.ts first. Find where human and API job prompts are built.

For human steps, update the prompt to include notification channels:
```typescript
// After building the base prompt
if (step.notificationChannels && step.notificationChannels.length > 0) {
  prompt += '\n\nNotification Channels:\n';
  for (const ch of step.notificationChannels) {
    prompt += `- ${ch.kind}: ${ch.target}${ch.label ? ` (${ch.label})` : ''}\n`;
  }
}
if (step.timeoutValue && step.timeoutUnit) {
  prompt += `\nTimeout: ${step.timeoutValue} ${step.timeoutUnit}\n`;
}
```

For API steps with integration info, update the prompt:
```typescript
if (step.integrationId) {
  prompt += `\nIntegration: ${step.integrationName ?? step.integrationId}\n`;
  if (step.objectTypeId) prompt += `Object Type: ${step.objectTypeId}\n`;
  if (step.action) prompt += `Action: ${step.action}\n`;
}
```

